    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p><persName>S. GERSTMAN &amp; CO.</persName>,</p>
            <p>Commission Merchants</p>
            <p>
                <placeName>186 Congress &amp; 85 St. Julian Sts.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>SAVANNAH, GA</placeName>.</p>
            <p><persName role="author">S. GERSTMAN</persName>. <persName>W. BARNETT</persName>.</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Savannah</placeName>, <date>April 17 1866</date></p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)">Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I have recd the<lb/> Tafelas &amp;c and have collected<lb/> all the
                money except for<lb/> two which the party are not<lb/> in town but will be here<lb/>
                in a few days, when I will<lb/> forward you a draft for<lb/> the full amount, I
                would<lb/> advise you if possible to<lb/> come out to inaugurate the<lb/> B.B. Lodge
                here as I am confident<lb/> that you could get over 50<lb/> subscribers for the
                Occident<lb/> &amp; could sell over 100 copies<lb/> of your daily Prayers, and
                probably</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>some other of your publications.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have the Honor to be very</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Respectfully yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Brother <persName role="author">Phillip Walker</persName></p>
            <p>P.S. Brother <persName>Gartensteig</persName> send<lb/> his thanks for your attention
                to the<lb/> payment of his dues, you will<lb/> please send the <persName
                    role="author">Rev. Simon Gerstman</persName><lb/> a set of <add>Hebrew?</add>
                polish minhag<lb/> with english translation, also<lb/>
                <del>for</del> one <sic>sett</sic> Portuguese <add>Hebrew?</add><lb/> and also one
                prayer book for<lb/>
                <add>Hebrew?</add> with english since<lb/> writing the above I have recd the<lb/>
                balance of the money $ 20.00 is for<lb/> the 2 Bibles $25.00 for the other<lb/>
                Books &amp; $4.00 for <persName role="author">Rev. Simon<lb/> Gerstmans</persName>
                Occident for which you<lb/> will please acknowledge receipt</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p><addressee>Rev Mr. Leeser</addressee>!</p>
            <p>As personally unknown each other,<lb/> I would respectfully ask of you<lb/> to send
                me some manuscripts,<lb/> of your works, or talmudical,<lb/> also different
                    <sic>adresses</sic> delivered<lb/> by you, and different subjects.<lb/> I should
                be very obliging to<lb/> you. You can send them to<lb/> me per express, such as you
                think<lb/> will be useful to me. You can<lb/> send them along when you send<lb/> me
                the other books.</p>
            <p><sic>Hopping</sic> to hear from you<lb/> by return.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I remain Rev</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your most good servant</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName role="author">Simon Gerstmann</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
